Reasoning: The paper deals with the computational complexity of maximizing the H-index using article merges, which involves graph theory and optimization algorithms. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Among these, cs.DS and cs.AI are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the technical aspects of the paper, while cs.IR, cs.CY, and cs.SI are more tangentially related to the social and ethical implications of H-index manipulation.
